President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Yuri Kim of Guam as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Albania. Kim is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has held various positions within the Department of State, including Director of the Office of Southern European Affairs and Director of the State Department's Center for the Study of Diplomacy. She has also served in Iraq and Turkey as a Political Counselor at the United States Embassy. Kim holds a B.A. from the University of Pennsylvania and an M.Phil. from Cambridge University, and is fluent in Korean, Mandarin Chinese, Japanese, and Turkish.